 :tx/rationale "C9-AGENT-IDENTITY-FINAL: Implementation spec for automatic per-process agent identity (C9-P4). PROBLEM: All observations from parallel subagents get the same AgentId because they all use the default --agent braid:user. The agreement detection correctly requires 2+ agents so returns empty. SOLUTION: Three-tier resolution in the observe command dispatch (mod.rs): (1) Explicit --agent flag overrides everything. (2) BRAID_AGENT env var for orchestrated subagents. (3) Auto-derived from PID: format braid:pid-{PID}. Unique per process, stable within session, zero ceremony. ALSO: Session auto-detect in main.rs:136-158 should use the same resolved agent ID when creating the session entity, so :session/agent matches the observation agent. WHERE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs observe dispatch (line ~2633), and other command dispatches that accept --agent. Also main.rs session auto-detect. SUBSTRATE-INDEPENDENT: No provider-specific logic. PID is universal. Env var is universal. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Two parallel braid observe from different PIDs produce different AgentIds. (B) Sequential commands from same PID produce same AgentId. (C) Explicit --agent overrides. (D) BRAID_AGENT env var overrides PID. (E) find_agreement_clusters returns non-empty when two PIDs observe same finding."
